This paper is about the complexity of planning problems, which is a central topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on planning problems characterized by unary operators and directed path causal graphs, which falls under the subfield of planning (cs.PL). The paper also involves analyzing the complexity of the problem, which is related to computational complexity theory (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the structure of causal graphs, which is related to the subfield of logic (cs.LO) and the analysis of graphs (cs.DS).
